---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="RCAN Protocol" description="RCAN - Robot Communication & Addressing Network. An open protocol for addressing, discovering, and authenticating robotic agents.">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>RCAN Protocol</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Robot Communication & Addressing Network</p>
    <p class="subtitle">An open, federated protocol for addressing, discovering, and authenticating robotic agents across local networks and the internet.</p>
    
    <div class="cta-buttons">
      <a href="/spec/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Spec</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/continuonai/rcan-spec" class="btn btn-secondary" rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <section class="intro">
    <h2>Why RCAN?</h2>
    <p>
      The internet has DNS and ICANN. IoT has Matter. <strong>Robotics has nothing.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      As millions of robots are manufactured and deployed‚Äîfrom warehouse arms to delivery bots to humanoids‚Äîthere is no standard way to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Address</strong> a robot uniquely and globally</li>
      <li><strong>Authenticate</strong> who is allowed to control it</li>
      <li><strong>Coordinate</strong> fleets and swarms across manufacturers</li>
      <li><strong>Ensure safety</strong> when networks fail or control transfers</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      RCAN is an open protocol specification designed to solve these problems with a federated, offline-resilient architecture.
    </p>
  </section>
  
  <section class="features">
    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üîó Robot URI (RURI)</h3>
        <p>Globally unique identifiers for every robot, similar to URLs for websites.</p>
        <code>rcan://continuon.cloud/continuon/companion-v1/d3a4b5c6</code>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üîê Role-Based Access</h3>
        <p>Five-level hierarchy: Guest ‚Üí User ‚Üí Leasee ‚Üí Owner ‚Üí Creator. Each role has explicit permissions.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üì° Local Discovery</h3>
        <p>mDNS/DNS-SD discovery via <code>_rcan._tcp.local</code>. Works offline when cloud is unreachable.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üõ°Ô∏è Safety Invariants</h3>
        <p>Local safety always wins. Network loss triggers safe-stop. All commands are audited.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>üåê Federated Registries</h3>
        <p>Like email servers, anyone can run an RCAN registry. No single point of control.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>ü§ñ Fleet Coordination</h3>
        <p>Choreographed multi-robot commands, swarm discovery, and conflict resolution.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="quick-start">
    <h2>Quick Example</h2>
    
    <pre><code class="language-python"># Connect to a robot via RCAN
from rcan import RURI, RCANClient, Role

# Parse the robot's address
ruri = RURI.parse("rcan://continuon.cloud/continuon/companion-v1/d3a4b5c6")

# Connect and authenticate
client = RCANClient(client_id="my-app")
await client.connect(ruri)
token = await client.claim(Role.USER, credential="my-key")

# Send a command
result = await client.command("/arm", "move", &#123;x: 0.5, y: 0.2&#125;)

# Clean up
await client.release()</code></pre>
  </section>
  
  <section class="links">
    <h2>Documentation</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/spec/">Full Specification</a> ‚Äî Complete protocol definition with schemas</li>
      <li><a href="/conformance/">Conformance Tests</a> ‚Äî Test suite for implementations</li>
      <li><a href="/implementations/">Reference Implementations</a> ‚Äî Python, TypeScript, Dart code</li>
      <li><a href="https://craigmerry.com/blog/2026-01-02-we-need-an-icann-for-robotics/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Blog: We Need an ICANN for Robotics</a> ‚Äî The rationale behind RCAN</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

